yer|first=Ochai|last=Agbaji|link=y|num=30|pos=G|ft=6|in=5|lbs=210|class=JR|rs=|home=[[Kansas City, Missouri|Kansas City, MO]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=David|last=McCormack|num=33|pos=C|ft=6|in=10|lbs=265|class=JR|rs=|home=[[Norfolk, Virginia|Norfolk, VA]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Mitch|last=Lightfoot|num=44|pos=F|ft=6|in=8|lbs=225|class=SR|rs=yes|home=[[Gilbert, Arizona|Gilbert, AZ]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Footer\n|head_coach=\n* [[Bill Self]] ({{college|Oklahoma State}})\n|asst_coach=\n* [[Norm Roberts]] ([[Queens College, City University of New York|Queens (NY)]])\n* [[Kurtis Townsend]] ({{college|Western Kentucky}})\n* [[Jerrance Howard]] ({{college|Illinois}})\n|roster_url=http://www.kuathletics.com/roster.aspx?path=mbball&\n|accessdate= April 13, 2020\n}}\n\n==Schedule and results==\nThe Jayhawks full non-conference schedule will be announced in the summer. They will play Division II Kansas schools Washburn and Emporia State in exhibition games. The Jayhawks will also renew their [[Border War (Kansas\u2013Missouri rivalry)|rivalry with Missouri]] with a game at the [[Sprint Center]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Kansas Athletics announces multi-year agreement to reignite Border Showdown rivalry |url=https://kuathletics.com/kansas-athletics-announces-multi-year-agreement-to-reignite-border-showdown-rivalry/ |website=KUAthletics.com|date=October 22, 2019 }}</ref> The Jayhawks will also play Kentucky in the [[Champions Classic]].<ref>{{cite web |title=2020 Matchups |url= https://espnevents.com/champions-classic/matchup/ |website=ESPNEvents.com}}</ref> The Jayhawks will also participate in the [[Big 12/SEC Challenge]] and [[Big East\u2013Big 12 Alliance]] with their opponent in both to be determined. Additionally, as they do every season, they will play every Big 12 opponent at home and on the road and will be guaranteed at least one game in the 2021 Big 12 Tournament, if they are not banned from postseason play with their pending discipline from the NCAA.\n\n{{CBB sched