Fame head coach [[Bill Self]]. Due to pending disciplinary action from the NCAA, the Jayhawks NCAA record 30 consecutive NCAA Tournament streak may be in jeopardy of ending.\n\n==Roster changes==\n===Graduation===\nBelow are players who graduated from the University of Kansas without any college eligibility left.\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Name !! Position\n|-\n| [[Udoka Azubuike]] || C\n|-\n| Isaiah Moss || G\n|}\n\n===Early draft entrants===\n{{see also|2020 NBA draft}}\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Name !! Position !! Class !! Stayed in<br>draft\n|-\n| [[Devon Dotson]] || Guard || Sophomore || TBD\n|}\n\n===Recruiting class===\n{{College athlete recruit start|40=no|collapse=no|year=2018}}\n{{College athlete recruit entry\n| recruit  = Bryce Thompson\n| position = G\n| hometown = Tulsa, OK\n| highschool = Booker T. Washington\n| feet   = 6\n| inches = 4\n| weight = 180\n| 40     =\n| commitdate = 11/12/2019\n| scout stars  = \n| rivals stars = 5\n| 247 stars = 5\n| espn grade = 90\n}}\n{{College athlete recruit entry\n| recruit  = Gethro Muscadin \n| position = C\n| hometown = Louisville, KY\n| highschool = Aspire Academy\n| feet   = 6\n| inches = 10\n| weight = 215\n| 40     =\n| commitdate = 10/17/2019\n| scout stars  = \n| rivals stars = 4\n| 247 stars = 3\n| espn grade = 80\n}}\n{{College athlete recruit entry\n| recruit  = Latrell Josell \n| position = G\n| hometown = Keller, TX\n| highschool = Central\n| feet   = 6\n| inches = 0\n| weight = 160\n| 40     =\n| commitdate = 11/14/2019\n| scout stars  = \n| rivals stars = 3\n| 247 stars = 3\n| espn grade = 77\n}}\n|-\n| colspan=\"7\" style=\"padding-left:10px;\" | '''Overall recruiting rankings:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[[247Sports|247 Sports]]: '''16'''&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;[[Rivals.com|Rivals]]: '''12'''&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;  [[ESPN]]: '''20'''&nbsp;\n|}\n<!-- Do not add recruiting class of 2021 to this page as it has no relevance to this season. Wait until 2021-2022 article is created after the season is over and add it in that article-->\n\n===Transfers===\n\n====Incoming====\n{| class=\"wikitable\"\n! Name !! Position !! Class !! Old School\n|-\n| Tyon Grant-Foster || G || JR || [[Indian Hills Community College|Indian Hills CC]]\n|}\n\n==Roster==\nThis is a preliminary roster based on the 2019\u201320 roster with seniors removed and incoming freshmen and transfers added. This roster will undergo multiple changes prior to the start of the season as players declare for the draft, transfer in or out, walk-ons are added or removed, and high school seniors commit or decommit. The roster will not be finalized until the fall.\n\n<!-- HEIGHTS, WEIGHTS, AND POSITIONS ARE BASED ON KU'S ROSTER ON THEIR WEBSITE AT http://www.kuathletics.com/roster.aspx?path=mbball, ANY OTHER WEIGHTS, HEIGHT, AND POSITIONS ARE INACCURATE AND SHOULD NOT BE INCLUDED -->\n{{CBB roster/Header|year=2020|team=Kansas Jayhawks|teamcolors=y}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Tyon|last=Grant-Foster|num=--|pos=F|ft=6|in=6|lbs=190|class=JR|rs=|home=[[Ottumwa, Iowa|Ottumwa, IA]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Latrell|last=Jossel|num=--|pos=G|ft=6|in=0|lbs=160|class=FR|rs=|home=[[Keller, Texas|Keller, TX]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Gethro|last=Muscadin|num=--|pos=C|ft=6|in=10|lbs=215|class=FR|rs=|home=[[Louisville, Kentucky|Louisville, KY]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Bryce|last=Thompson|num=--|pos=G|ft=6|in=4|lbs=180|class=FR|rs=|home=[[Tulsa, Oklahoma|Tulsa, OK]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Marcus|last=Garrett|link=y|num=0|pos=G|ft=6|in=5|lbs=195|class=SR|rs=|home=[[Dallas|Dallas, TX]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Devon|last=Dotson|link=y|num=1|pos=G|ft=6|in=2|lbs=185|class=JR|rs=|home=[[Charlotte, North Carolina|Charlotte, NC]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Christian|last=Braun|num=2|pos=F|ft=6|in=6|lbs=205|class=SO|rs=|home=[[Overland Park, Kansas|Overland Park, KS]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Dajuan|last=Harris|num=3|pos=G|ft=6|in=1|lbs=160|class=SO|rs=|home=[[Columbia, Missouri|Columbia, MO]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Elijah|last=Elliott|num=5|pos=G|ft=6|in=3|lbs=185|class=SO|rs=yes|home=[[Southlake, Texas|Southlake, TX]]|note=W}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Jalen|last=Wilson|num=10|pos=F|ft=6|in=8|lbs=215|class=SO|rs=|home=[[Denton, Texas|Denton, TX]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Chris|last=Teahan|num=12|pos=G|ft=6|in=4|lbs=195|class=SR|rs=|home=[[Leawood, Kansas|Leawood, KS]]|note=W}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Tristan|last=Enaruna|link=y|num=13|pos=G/F|ft=6|in=8|lbs=200|class=SO|rs=|home=[[Almere|Almere, Netherlands]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Michael|last=Jankovich|num=20|pos=G|ft=6|in=5|lbs=185|class=SO|rs=|home=[[Dallas|Dallas, TX]]|note=W}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Silvio|last=De Sousa|link=y|num=22|pos=F|ft=6|in=9|lbs=245|class=SR|rs=|home=[[Luanda|Luanda, Angola]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Ochai|last=Agbaji|link=y|num=30|pos=G|ft=6|in=5|lbs=210|class=JR|rs=|home=[[Kansas City, Missouri|Kansas City, MO]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=David|last=McCormack|num=33|pos=C|ft=6|in=10|lbs=265|class=JR|rs=|home=[[Norfolk, Virginia|Norfolk, VA]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Player|first=Mitch|last=Lightfoot|num=44|pos=F|ft=6|in=8|lbs=225|class=SR|rs=yes|home=[[Gilbert, Arizona|Gilbert, AZ]]}}\n{{CBB roster/Footer\n|head_coach=\n* [[Bill Self]] ({{college|Oklahoma State}})\n|asst_coach=\n* [[Norm Roberts]] ([[Queens College, City University of New York|Queens (NY)]])\n* [[Kurtis Townsend]] ({{college|Western Kentucky}})\n* [[Jerrance Howard]] ({{college|Illinois}})\n|roster_url=http://www.kuathletics.com/roster.aspx?path=mbball&\n|accessdate= March 15, 2020\n}}\n\n==Schedule and results==\nThe Jayhawks full non-conference schedule will be announced in the summer. They will play Division II Kansas schools Washburn and Emporia State in exhibition games. The Jayhawks will also renew their [[Border War (Kansas\u2013Missouri rivalry)|rivalry with Missouri]] with a game at the [[Sprint Center]].<ref>{{cite web |title=Kansas Athletics announces multi-year agreement to reignite Border Showdown rivalry |url=https://kuathletics.com/kansas-athletics-announces-multi-year-agreement-to-reignite-border-showdown-rivalry/ |website=KUAthletics.com|date=October 22, 2019 }}</ref> The Jayhawks will also play Kentucky in the [[Champions Classic]].<ref>{{cite web |title=2020 Matchups |url= https://espnevents.com/champions-classic/matchup/ |website=ESPNEvents.com}}</ref> The Jayhawks will also participate in the [[Big 12/SEC Challenge]] and [[Big East\u2013Big 12 Alliance]] with their opponent in both to be determined. Additionally, as they do every season, they will play every Big 12 opponent at home and on the road and will be guaranteed at least one game in the 2021 Big 12 Tournament, if they are not banned from postseason play with their pending discipline from the NCAA.\n\n{{CBB schedule start|gamehighs=yes|attend=yes}}\n|-\n!colspan=12 style={{NCAA color cell|Kansas Jayhawks}}| Exhibition\n{{CBB schedule entry\n| date          = TBD\n| time          = TBD\n| w/l           = \n| nonconf       = yes\n| away          = \n| rank          = \n| opponent      = [[Washburn Ichabods men's basketball|Washburn]]\n| site_stadium  = [[Allen Fieldhouse]]\n| site_cityst   = [[Lawrence, Kansas|Lawrence, KS]]\n| tv            = TBD\n| highscorer    = &nbsp;\n| points        = \n| highrebounder = &nbsp;\n| rebounds      = \n| highassister  = &nbsp;\n| assists       = \n| score         = \n| attend        = \n| record        = \u2013\n}}\n{{CBB schedule entry\n| date          = TBD\n| time          = TBD\n| w/l           = \n| nonconf       = yes\n| away          = \n| rank          = \n| opponent      = [[Emporia State Hornets basketball|Emporia State]]\n| site_stadium  = Allen Fieldhouse\n| site_cityst   = Lawrence, KS\n| tv            = TBD\n| highscorer    = &nbsp;\n| points        = \n| highrebounder = &nbsp;\n| rebounds      = \n| highassister  = &nbsp;\n| assists       = \n| score         = \n| attend        = \n| record        = \u2013\n}}\n